Rating: 4
I have made this recipe many times and it is still a favorite - especially when I have fresh cabbage coming out of the garden. I use sweet Vidalia onions, Dijon country-style mustard and extra hot horseradish. Easy and healthy.

Rating: 4
I only had a small head of geriatric cabbage - so rather than just wilt it, I let it cook at a low simmer for longer. I added more horseradish, as suggested, and a bit of Dijon to the coarse-grained mustard for more bite. I also added the sauce to the cabbage for the last 10 or 15 minutes of cooking. It was delicious and I would certainly serve it to cabbage-loving guests - it could easily be made the day before and re-heated. It felt virtuous as well - up until we tried this recipe our favourite cabbage dish included heavy cream and bacon! a keeper.

